<p>I wanted to nest a variable inside an <code>ng-include</code>. The variable in this case would be a CDN path or file path. This works:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;img src="{{cdn}}uploads/avatar_{{uid}}.png" ng-src="{{cdn}}uploads/avatar_{{uid}}.png" /&gt; </code></pre>  <p>This does not</p>  <pre><code>&lt;div ng-controller="expr"&gt;   &lt;div ng-include="'{{cdn}}logo.tpl'"&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;/div&gt; </code></pre>  <p>This would really help in my template views and routes. I don't want to use directives.</p>